\name{vdl_version}
\alias{vdl_version}
\title{Get the vennDiagramLab package version}
\description{
Returns the installed version of vennDiagramLab as a character string.
This trivial function exists so the Phase 0 skeleton has one public
export; Phase 1 introduces the real \code{analyze()} / \code{load_*()} API.
}
\usage{
vdl_version()
}
\value{
Character string, the package version (e.g. "2.0.0").
}
\examples{
vdl_version()
}
